An Act relative to cellular coverage.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. The department of telecommunications and cable shall consult with cell
2 phone carriers operating within the commonwealth to identify the cell tower and antenna site
3 infrastructure improvements necessary to provide cellular coverage to all residents of the
4 commonwealth.
5 SECTION 2. The department of telecommunications and cable, in consultation with the
6 department of capital asset management and maintenance, shall identify parcels of
7 commonwealth or municipal-owned land that could be sold, leased or licensed to cell phone
8 carriers at discounted or nominal consideration for the purposes of constructing or facilitating the
9 construction of additional cell towers or antenna sites in areas where cellular coverage is
10 currently unavailable. If such commonwealth or municipal-owned land does not exist in certain
11 areas where cellular coverage is currently unavailable, the department of telecommunications
12 and cable, in consultation with the department of capital asset management and maintenance,
13 shall also identify parcels that could be purchased or leased by the commonwealth for the
1 of 2

14 purposes of leasing or licensing the parcel to a cell phone carrier for discounted or nominal
15 consideration.
16 SECTION 3. Not later than January 1, 2030, the department of telecommunications and
17 cable shall ensure that all residents of the commonwealth are able to access cellular coverage
18 with their mobile device regardless of their location.
19 SECTION 4. Not later than July 30, 2026, the department of telecommunications and
20 cable shall submit to the clerks of the house of representatives and the senate, the house and
21 senate committees on ways and means and the joint committee on telecommunications, utilities
22 and energy a report including its plan for improving cell tower and antenna site infrastructure,
23 any land identified pursuant section 2 and progress on its goal of improving cellular coverage in
24 the commonwealth.
